added.title: Titan Saving Time
added.description: The Titans are determined to find out what happened to the missing 2'oclock hour during Daylight Saving Time.

added.title: Cool School
added.description: Rose Wilson escapes from prison defeating the Titans with cool one liners. Only Raven is immune to Rose's insults, and the two decide to hang out and do cool stuff together. Cyborg, Starfire and Beast Boy feel lame by comparison so they go to Cool School.

added.title: Double Trouble
added.description: Cyborg and Beast Boy create clones of themselves to do their chores and the clones create more clones until the situation grows out of control.

added.title: The Lady
added.description: When Gumball and Darwin track a women emerging from their home, they discover her to be a member of a gang of wise-cracking elderly friends. However, as they get closer and closer to her life, they realize they may know her already.

added.title: The Vegging
added.description: Gumball and Darwin want to have a lazy day on the sofa, and have come up with various tricks to stop themselves having to move. Gradually more and more people arrive, seemingly to get them to move, until finally they realize that if they have to move, they'll do it in the laziest way possible.

added.title: The Father
added.description: When Frankie attends a party at The Watterson's he realizes it's a holiday Granny Jojo made up to celebrate the day he left. Richard is feeling sad about the years he lost with Frankie so the kids try anything to cheer him up.

added.title: The Cage
added.description: When Mr. Corneille shows up to work with a mysterious bruise, Gumball and Darwin discover that he's teacher by day and a cage fighter by night, or was until he vowed never to fight again. However, when the school is being closed for a lack of finances the boys have to try and convince him to come out retirement for one last fight.

added.title: The Candidate
added.description: When their parents all go to a charity gala at the school, the kids are locked in a classroom with a VHS tape. However, when the room starts to heat up, they need a leader to get them out of the situation and have to choose between Anais, a qualified but unpopular candidate or Gumball, a charismatic candidate with absolutely no plans.

added.title: Gem Harvest
added.description: Steven's autumn visit to the barn brings a new stranger into his life.

added.title: Hit the Diamond
added.description: Steven and the Gems play an old fashioned game of baseball.

added.title: Gem Hunt
added.description: Steven and Connie track a Gem monster through the wilderness but its tracks lead them to mystery.

added.title: Historical Friction
added.description: Steven and Jamie put on a play about the founding of Beach City.

added.title: Gem Glow
added.description: Steven thinks his favorite ice cream sandwiches are the trick to summoning his magic shield but learns otherwise when facing off with an acid-spewing insect monster.

added.title: Christmas in Space
added.description: The guys celebrate their first Christmas in space by opening presents, eating peppermint bark and telling Christmas stories. Benson wants the stories to be more Christmas-y but the guys keep adding scary elements, which only infuriate their boss.

added.title: Crazy Fake Plan
added.description: Rigby has to create a massively crazy fake plan in order to surprise Eileen for the first time ever.

added.title: Chili Cook-Off
added.description: Benson wants to get some street cred with the Park Managers' Association and win the big chili cook-off.

added.title: Cube Bros
added.description: Muscle Man wants to prove he's more than just super buff so he gets a job in a corporate office.

added.title: Wake Up
added.description: In order to find Finn's father, Finn and Jame must commit a cosmic crime...unless the Lich beats them to it.

added.title: Hiccup Havok
added.description: Uncle Grandpa helps a kid who can't get rid of the hiccups.

added.title: MacGuffin
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and a kid embark on a dangerous jungle adventure in search of a legendary MacGuffin.

added.title: Sons of Mars
added.description: A case of Martian mistaken identity comes to Ooo when Magic Man turns Jake into a copy of himself.

added.title: You Made Me
added.description: When a creepy sleep-peeping Lemongrab upsets PB with his creepy ways, Finn & Jake need to tend to some issues in the Outer Realm.

added.title: Merry Christmas
added.description: When the Rustbucket's A/C goes on the fritz in the middle of the desert, Ben, Max and Gwen take refuge at Holiday Village, an over the top Christmas theme park that seems to appear out of nowhere. The place is run by an evil entity known as Mr. Jingles, who takes Max prisoner because he believes Max is Santa! It's up to Ben and Gwen to free Max and break the spell Mr. Jingles has cast on Holiday Village, freeing others who've been trapped their for years and releasing the theme park.

added.title: Tree of Life
added.description: Clarence, Jeff and Sumo make it their mission to climb a really tall tree before it's set to be chopped down. As they scale higher and higher their reality begins to slip away.

added.title: Creepy Doll/Death Metal Crash Pit
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby discover an old Victorian Doll that Pop's has not played with or seen since he was a child and unwittingly unleash its pent up rage against him.  Muscle Man and High Five Ghost want to crash an old RV into a pit, but it's haunted by an 80s death metal band.

added.title: Another Way
added.description: The tears of a crying Cyclops just might heal Finn and Jake's broken toes.

added.title: The Big Game
added.description: Chad takes Clarence to his first big game! Clarence takes it all in - the crack of the bat, the touchdown dances, the slam-dunks and of course, hotdogs and popcorn! But will Clarence get to fulfill his dream of meeting Aberdale's beloved mascot?

added.title: Sideline Dad
added.description: When the Girls start playing soccer, the Professor goes overboard.

added.title: Green Wing
added.description: When volunteering at a retirement home, Buttercup meets an old woman who claims she used to be a superhero.

added.title: Ghostfreaked Out
added.description: Ben's internal demons get externalized when Ghostfreak escapes from his watch and becomes a full fledged being on his own. The renegade alien then realizes he needs to meld with Ben's DNA in order to survive.

added.title: The Substitute
added.description: After Ms. Baker takes an unexpected personal day, she is replaced by a substitute that has a hard time handling the unruly classroom. Soon, the school day devolves into chaos and it is up to Clarence to get Mrs. Baker back to where she belongs, the classroom.

added.title: Tree Trunks
added.description: Finn and Jake must take charge after the businessmen they've outsourced some of their work to go too far.

added.title: Horn, Sweet Horn
added.description: Bubbles convinces the Professor to test his new transmogrifying ray on her new friend Donny the Pony in an effort to help him become the unicorn he's always wanted to be. But when it turns Donny into a monster instead, she must stop him before he destroys Townsville!

added.title: Bye Bye, Bellum
added.description: The Mayor becomes dependent on the Powerpuff Girls after his assistant Ms. Bellum departs, leaving the girls so busy they accidentally hire the dangerous Bianca Bikini as his new assistant! When Bianca captures the Powerpuff Girls, the Mayor finds the tables turned and must rely on himself to help them.

added.title: So Long, and Thanks for All the Smoothies
added.description: When Ben and Rook investigate a mysterious alien ghost ship, they discover that Argit and the Vreedle Brothers are fighting for possession of a doomsday device! (Introducing Solid Plugg.)

added.title: Of Predators and Prey Part 1
added.description: After a heated argument, Ben and Rook go their separate ways, giving Khyber the Huntsman his best chance to capture Ben! (Introducing Dr. Psychobos, new Nemetrix aliens Mucillator & Terroranchula; new Ben alien Ballweevil.)

added.title: Lucky Girl
added.description: Ben battles an evil sorcerer whose power whose emanates from mystic charms, one of which turns Gwen into her own superhero named Lucky Girl.

added.title: Outbreak
added.description: When Dr. Psychobos steals a part out of the Omnitrix, causing chaotic side effects, it's up to Ben, Rook, and a small team of Plumbers get everything back to normal. (Introducing new Ben alien Kickin' Hawk, temp Ben alien Walkatrout, Upchuck Rook.)

added.title: Many Happy Returns
added.description: Gwen and Kevin pay Ben a surprise visit, but does Kevin's strange behavior have anything to do with an angry Tetramand princess, or her father's fleet of warships prepared to attack the Earth?

added.title: Malefactor
added.description: Khyber and his dog attacks Ben and Rook while they're at the "Olde Bellwood Days" festival, but does the hunter have other plans? (Introducing new Nemetrix alien Hypnotick.)

added.title: Bad Morning
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa wakes up on the wrong side of the bed, he changes into a grumpy grump and it's up to the rest of the gang to reverse his bad day.

added.title: Bezt Frends
added.description: Uncle Grandpa goes to extreme measures to surpass Pizza Steve as Pizza Steve's best friend.

added.title: People Pleaser
added.description: Blossom neglects her promise to Bubbles when she takes on too many things leaving Buttercup and Bubbles to fend for themselves.

added.title: Ballin'
added.description: Uncle Grandpa, Pizza Steve, and Mr. Gus must win a basketball game against a super awesome b-ball crew in order to keep the RV.

removed.title: Mystery Train
removed.description: Finn and Jake get wrapped up in a high speed whodunit!

removed.title: Earthlings
removed.description: Amethyst tries to exact revenge with a showdown in the Kindergarten.

removed.title: Princess Buttercup
removed.description: When Buttercup starts spending a lot of time with her new friends, a group of bad-girl skaters called The Derbytantes, it seems the Powerpuff Girls are down to two, which delights Princess Morbucks, who wants to fill the empty slot.

removed.title: Are You Talking to Tree?
removed.description: When the tree inside the RV begins talking to Uncle Grandpa, he must convince the gang that he's not going crazy.

removed.title: Friend Ship
removed.description: The Crystal Gems explore an ancient Gem spaceship.

removed.title: The More Things Change Part 1
removed.description: Now on his own, Ben sets out to be a solo superhero, with new alien heroes at his disposal, but Grandpa Max has other plans. (Introducing Rook, Malware, Khyber, Nemetrix alien Crabdozer, new Ben aliens Feedback & Blox, Pakmar.)

removed.title: Third Time's a Charm
removed.description: Charmaster returns to exact her revenge on Gwendolyn once and for all.

removed.title: A Jolt from the Past
removed.description: Alien pests from Ben's youth come back, but now they need Ben's help. (Introducing Fistrick, & new Ben alien Gravattack.)

removed.title: Nemesis
removed.description: A shadowy figure named Peace Master targets the Candy Kingdom elite.

removed.title: Future Boy Zoltron
removed.description: Steven fills in for a fortune teller at Funland.

removed.title: The Secret of Dos Santos
removed.description: Ben and Rook join Kai Green on a perilous alien relic hunt through South America.

removed.title: Painbow
removed.description: When a mysterious rainbow causes everyone to become unnaturally happy, the Powerpuff Girls must find where it ends to save the day and return Townsville to normal.

removed.title: Watch It!
removed.description: The Powerpuff Girls are tasked with keeping a priceless gem safe from thieves.

removed.title: Full Disclosure
removed.description: Steven tries to avoid Connie so he doesn't have to tell her about his most recent harrowing adventure.

removed.title: Movie Night
removed.description: It's Movie Night and the Titans have a hard time deciding who gets to choose which movie they watch.

removed.title: Dignity of Teeth
removed.description: When Beast Boy gets a stack of cash from the Tooth Fairy, against Raven's advice the other Titans start knocking out their own teeth to get some of that sweet Tooth Fairy money.

removed.title: It Was Them
removed.description: Dr. Animo has escaped his Plumber prison, and Ben and Rook must track him down before he turns the world into his personal mutant ant farm! (Introducing Nemetrix alien Slamworm, Galvan Plumbers Blukic and Driba, Arctiguana, new Ben alien Crashhopper.)

removed.title: 1992 Called
removed.description: Uncle Grandpa travels back to the year 1492 to retrieve a pair of pants.

removed.title: Ben 4 Good Buddy
removed.description: Out on a desert highway, a group of modern day highway pirates hijack the Rustbucket, trick it out and use it in a daring robbery. And while Ben and Gwen are at first glad to get rid of that "bucket of bolts", they come to realize the Rustbucket is "a part of the family." In the end our trio heroes get Max's beloved "ride" back and bring down these pirates once and for all.

removed.title: Don't Drink the Water
removed.description: In Florida, Ben and Max accidentally come in contact with water from The Fountain of Youth. As a result, Max transforms into a kid and Ben a toddler, with Gwen having to deal with both of them. Our trio then must track down Hex who's found the source of the fountain and prevent him from drinking the water that will make him immortal and unstoppable.

removed.title: Spice Game
removed.description: Tired of Robin's bland cooking, the other Titans try their hand at spicing up their food.

removed.title: Anger Management
removed.description: Aunt Grandma's back is causing more trouble for Uncle Grandpa.

removed.title: The Oct-Father
removed.description: When Princess Morbucks steals Octi, Bubbles' reaction surprises everyone, even her sisters.

removed.title: Afraid of the Dark
removed.description: When UG helps a little girl who is afraid of the dark, he convinces her there's nothing to be afraid of but their imaginations.  But when their imaginations prove to be pretty terrifying, they go on a quest to turn on the lights.

removed.title: Puhoy
removed.description: Stuck inside the treehouse during a sword storm, Jake builds a pillow fort while Finn goes to a different world.

removed.title: The Stayover
removed.description: After going overboard on the candy, Blossom and Buttercup wake up with no memory of last night and no idea where Bubbles is! They must piece together the events of last night and find Bubbles before the Professor gets back!

removed.title: Divided We Stand
removed.description: While at the beach, Ben discovers a new hero, Ditto, and soon has the ability to create multiple Dittos at once. removed.description: The gang must stop a nefarious imposter from rendering Uncle Grandpa obsolete.

removed.title: Gem Drill
removed.description: Steven takes a journey deep underground.

removed.title: Ricardio the Heart Guy
removed.description: Finn becomes jealous of Princes Bubblegum's new suitor.

removed.title: Ocean of Fear
removed.description: Finn faces his biggest challenge yet...overcoming his fear of water.

removed.title: T.K.O.
removed.description: Searching for power, KO accepts the help of a mysterious figure. Our heroes band together to save the plaza from a new menace.
